<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="idx-titlesoffices" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Titles, offices, political posts, honorifics, occupations</head>
    <p>Tagging of different types of offices, posts, titles etc.</p>
    <p>
        <specList>
            <specDesc key="w"/>
            <specDesc key="rs"/>
        </specList>
    </p>
    
    <p>Titles, offices, posts etc. in the text could be extracted from the vocabulary. They can be tagged using the @lemma attribute of the <gi>w</gi>.</p> 
    <!-- can have div's or p's  here. Divs are for subsections. -->
    
        
        <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
            <w lemma="consul"><expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan></w>
        </egXML>
    
    <p>Another way to do it could be using the <gi>rs</gi> element with @type="office" and a @key or a @ref pointing to an authority list.</p>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="http://insaph.kcl.ac.uk/iaph2007/iAph120644.html">
            <rs type="official" key="archon">ἀρχόντων</rs>
        </egXML>
    
    
